Since his mother bore a new sibling, his source of sustenance had vanished, leaving him gnawing endlessly on empty bottles. Driven by his quest for milk, he roamed the neighborhood each day seeking a replacement maternal figure. When an elderly couple arrived in town, Ellie's captivating presence made her his chosen target. Her aged husband could no longer fulfill marital expectations, leaving Ellie in constant frustration. One sunny afternoon during her garden dance, she remained unaware of the boy's gaze from the shadowed perimeter. During her break, he stealthily took her garments stay while her husband was absent. The boy rushed to her doorstep, offering his treasured companion in exchange for liquid sustenance. Ellie found the request innocent, felt compassion for the child, and granted his earnest appeal, finally obtaining his desired refreshment, he then noticed his older brother's arrival and quickly concealed himself. Witnessing his siblings action to Ellie, resentment bloomed in his heart. Soon, Ellie and her brother moved indoors, commencing private amusements, crushing the young boy's spirit. Creeping toward the chamber, he witnessed milky streams flowing beneath the doorway. Just as he prepared to enter and discover the source, Ellie's husband unexpectedly returned.

voice_to_text: The entwined pair on this barren isle were never romantic partners nor accidental strangers, but blood relatives who should have kept defined boundaries. Mel gripped her brother Dick's wrist, forcing his palm against her pelvis. The cold sweat on their skin concealed secret more lethal than pregnancy. They had already crossed the line siblings must never breach. That day, he spotted a vessel. His shouts proved futile. He urged Mel to light signal fires, but she refused. Stranded on this island for six years, she had long abandoned rescue hopes. Enraged, Dick confronted his sister. Taking provisions, he launched the raft while Mel watched from the shore. In the next moment, the craft was devoured by raging waves. This spectacle made Mel erupt in laughter. Returning to shore, Dick endured her taunts. Their argument reignited. In the heat of anger, Mel hurled a coconut, striking Dick's skull. Alarmed, she rushed to his side. But Dick rose and departed. Cast her belongings out of their shelter. With nowhere to retreat, Mel could only construct a crude refuge. However, the makeshift hut couldn't withstand the downpour. When Dick went hunting at dawn, he discovered his sister nearly lifeless. Scooping her into his arms, he carried her toward the ancient stone idol.
